Universal SonarQube Scanner for AK Projects (AK.Server, AK.Web, AK.Mobile)

Requires SONAR_TOKEN environment variable to be set.

Usage:
    python universal_scan.py server
    python universal_scan.py web origin/develop
    python universal_scan.py mobile --skip-tests

Setup:
    1. Generate token at http://localhost:9000 (User Account > Security > Tokens)
    2. Set environment variable: SONAR_TOKEN=sqa_your_token_here
    3. Run: python universal_scan.py <project>

Features:
    - Git integration (detects changed files vs target branch)
    - Separate source vs test files automatically
    - Supports .NET, Angular, and Flutter projects
    - Optional --skip-tests flag for code-only analysis
    - Single token for all projects (simplifies setup)

Security:
    - Uses environment variables (no hardcoded tokens)
    - Safe to commit to version control
    - Each developer uses their own token
